create branch

1) type: git checkout -b gh-pages     THis creates a new branch   - hit enter

	should say: switched to new branch gh-pages

2) open up .gitignore

type: open . in git
	drag folder into sublime
		go into the git ignore folder

3) remove public from the gitignore file
	save it

4) go to git
Type: git status
	you should see modified, public/ folder is Untracked files

5) Type: git add .gitignore
	git add public
		git status

Should show the public folders have been added in 

6) Type: git commit -m "adding the public folder"
	hit ENTER

7) Type: git branch
* beside branch we are currently on

Type: git push origin gh-pages
	Hit ENTER

you should see that in the remote repo is show gh pages in the new branch

8) Type: git push upstream gh-pages
	This creates a gh-pages branch on your organizations page on 

9) go to git hub
	click on organization repo
		should see new branch/pages


10) this branch is used for hosting out gh pages that has the public folder

11) go to settings - scroll to source - master branch, click gh-pages branch
	press save

12) git checkout master - siwthced you back to the master branch

